Interface BrowserElement

All Superinterfaces:
CanBeDisabled, CanBeEnabled, Nullable
All Known Subinterfaces:
Clickable, Selectable, TextEnterable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseBrowserElement, CheckBox, Component, DefaultDatePicker, Draggable, DropDown, Link, NullBrowserElement, RadioButton, TextArea, TextField, TinyMceEditor
public interface BrowserElement
extends CanBeEnabled, CanBeDisabled, Nullable

Interface to describe any element on a browser. The browser element may have other composite elements. A browser element may be enabled or disabled. This may be "null" if the requested element cannot be found on the browser. This class uses the Null Object Pattern. Unless absolutely needed do not make your page object implement this interface directly. Instead make them extend BaseBrowserElement.
